import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', kde=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    average_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    sns.barplot(x=['Average Rate'], y=[average_rate])
    plt.axhline(average_rate, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Rate: {average_rate:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average rate in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    missing_rate = data['rate'].isna().value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=missing_rate.index, y=missing_rate.values)
    plt.xlabel('Missing Rate Values')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('Are there any missing values in the rate field of the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
